<subSubSection pageId="33" pageNumber="34" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="33.[151,1437,152,359]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,152,179]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Distribution.</emphasis>
This species was previously recorded from 
<collectingCountry box="[852,998,153,179]" name="Saudi Arabia" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Saudi Arabia</collectingCountry>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Dawah, H. A. &amp; Abdullah, M. A." box="[1042,1347,153,180]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" pagination="182 - 192" refId="ref27734" refString="Dawah, H. A. &amp; Abdullah, M. A. (2006) New records of Chloropidae (Diptera) from Southwest Saudi Arabia with some biological information, world-wide geographical distribution and taxonomic features. Saudi Journal of Biological Science 13 (1), 182 - 192." type="journal article" year="2006">Dawah &amp; Abdullah (2006)</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="El-Hawagry, M. &amp; Khalil, M. W. &amp; Sharsf, M. R. &amp; Fadl, H. H. &amp; Aldawood, A. S." pageId="33" pageNumber="34" pagination="1 - 88" refId="ref28187" refString="El-Hawagry, M., Khalil, M. W., Sharsf, M. R., Fadl, H. H. &amp; Aldawood, A. S. (2013) A preliminary study on the insect fauna of Al-Baha Province, Saudi Arabia, with descriptions of two new species. Zookeys, 274, 1 - 88." type="journal article" year="2013">
El-Hawagry 
<emphasis box="[229,286,189,215]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">et al.</emphasis>
(2013)
</bibRefCitation>
. It was described from 
<collectingCountry box="[635,758,189,215]" name="Zimbabwe" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Zimbabwe</collectingCountry>
, and since recorded from 
<collectingCountry box="[1050,1126,189,215]" name="Kenya" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Kenya</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1138,1281,189,215]" name="South Africa" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">South Africa</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[1336,1437,189,215]" name="Tanzania" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Tanzania</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Sabrosky, C. W." box="[159,333,225,251]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" pagination="695 - 712" refId="ref29948" refString="Sabrosky, C. W. (1980) Family Chloropidae. In: Crosskey, R. W. (editor). Catalogue of the Diptera of the Afrotropical Region, pp. 695 - 712. British Museum (Natural History), London. 1437 pp." type="book chapter" year="1980">Sabrosky 1980</bibRefCitation>
). Material with individual puparia in NMWC was reared from the tunnels of a species of 
<taxonomicName authority="Guenee" authorityName="Guenee" authorityYear="1854" class="Insecta" family="Crambidae" genus="Parthenodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Parthenodes</emphasis>
Guenée
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" box="[324,466,261,287]" class="Insecta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="order">Lepidoptera</taxonomicName>
: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1810" box="[475,600,261,288]" class="Insecta" family="Crambidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Crambidae</taxonomicName>
) in bracken in 
<date box="[766,888,260,287]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" value="1985-04">April 1985</date>
from the Katberg, 
<collectingCountry box="[1102,1247,261,287]" name="South Africa" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">South Africa</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="33" pageNumber="34" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="33.[151,1437,152,359]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,297,323]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Remarks.</emphasis>
Larvae of species of 
<taxonomicName authority="Duda" authorityName="Duda" authorityYear="1933" box="[560,765,297,323]" class="Insecta" family="Chloropidae" genus="Polyodaspis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[560,697,297,323]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Polyodaspis</emphasis>
Duda
</taxonomicName>
feed on animal matter and are parasitoids or predacious on caterpillars and other insects. Some species are predators in mantids egg cases (
<bibRefCitation author="Ferrar, P. A." box="[1041,1178,333,359]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" refId="ref28498" refString="Ferrar, P. A. (1987) Guide to the breeding habits and immature stages of Diptera Cyclorrhapha, Entomonograph, (Part I: Text), Volume 8. E. J. Brill, Scandinavian press, Leiden, Copenhagan. 478 pp." type="book" year="1987">Ferrar 1987</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
